sogou-zhongkao.prep: 进入; 到…里面[出现348次)];表示状态的改变[出现347次)]

1.en: Never get out of the market just because you have lost patience or get into a market because your are anxious from waiting.
1.cn: 不要因失去耐心而出市，不要因焦虑等待而入市。

2.en: And this growth in fund size seems to translate into a deterioration of investment returns.
2.cn: 而这种基金规模的增长，似乎会转化为投资收益的下降。

3.en: Well, you know, we got into this in the beginning as a trade-off, they say, between the wetlands versus the ocean depth.
3.cn: 当然，那些专家说，我们之所以会在海中看到这些景象，是因为我们不得不在湿地和深海之间权衡取舍。

0.en: Anything to put a Democrat into the governor's mansion.
0.cn: 能让民主党人进入州长府邸就好。

1.en: Don't go into the radiation zone. Don't ask too many questions.
1.cn: 别进入辐射区。别问太多问题。

2.en: And there's no other way into the computer lab? No other way in.
2.cn: 没有其他途径进入电脑室了吗？没有。

3.en: Not locking into a path too early gave me an opportunity to go into a new and life changing field.
3.cn: 没有太早锁死自己的道路，让我有机会进入改变生活的全新领域。

4.en: I earned my Master's in Criminal Justice and got into the academy.
4.cn: 我拿到了犯罪学的硕士学位，顺利进入警校。

5.en: Our drones spotted her crossing the border into the United States.
5.cn: 我们的无人机侦察到她越过国界进入了美国境内

6.en: Odessa, what is it you call it when he goes into one of his little places?
6.cn: 那叫什么，当他又进入自己的世界的时候？

7.en: It's like I've stepped through a time warp into some sci-fi future.
7.cn: 就像进入了一个时间隧道，到达了科幻的世界。

8.en: Look at them. They're going into the human world, and they don't even look scared!
8.cn: 瞧他们，他们要进入人类世界却一点都不吓人。

9.en: Well, it is the gosh-darnedest thing. Hard-scrabble's letting us into the Scare program.
9.cn: 真是碰到鬼了呢。郝刻薄让我们进入惊吓课程。

10.en: There you go. Now any e-mail from Wolowitz will go right into your spam folder.
10.cn: 好了，现在所有沃尔伍兹发来的邮件都会直接进入垃圾箱。

11.en: You used the tunnels to infiltrate yourself into the White House, somehow conning your way into the blue sector, all to try and warn her?
11.cn: 你之前从隧道侵入白宫，还想办法进入到了蓝区，你做这些都是为了警告她吗

12.en: Now, this is important. Once the battery is removed, everything is gonna slam into emergency mode.
12.cn: 这一点很重要，电池一被移走，监狱进入紧急模式。

13.en: They could get uplifted into a mountain range and eroded away or carried along in an oceanic plate and subducted back into the Earth's mantle, melting your fossil into hot mush.
13.cn: 他们可能因为地壳上升成为山脉又被侵蚀流失或是随着大洋板块潜没又进入地幔，将你的化石熔化。

14.en: If we're gonna get out of here, we're gonna need to get into that watchtower. And to do that, I'm gonna need a few things.
14.cn: 想逃走就得进入那座了望台，所以需要几样东西。

15.en: That's why you guys put us into a safe place. That's not the safe place. That's a hole.
15.cn: 所以你们让我们进入安全地带。那不是什么安全地带，那只是个洞。

16.en: But the future, our future starts tomorrow at dawn. When we march together into the Capitol.
16.cn: 但未来我们的未来，将在明日黎明我们进入国会区之时峥嵘初现。

17.en: Okay, it's very faint, but I can still sense him in the building. Go into the light, Mr. Heckles!
17.cn: 很微弱，但我还可以感觉他在大楼里，进入光芒中，哈克先生！

18.en: Exactly. If we didn't do it, these students would never get into another institution.
18.cn: 没错，如果我们没有这样做的话，这些学生可能永远都不会有进入高校的机会。

19.en: We're already hearing this is gonna be a very long lockout. We're about to go into the nuclear winter of the NBA.
19.cn: 我们已经听说这将是一个长期的停摆，我们将进入NBA的严冬。
